  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [x] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (d89f6af 2022-06-24T00:13:35.614846Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script script/NonceTest.s.sol:NonceTest --private-key 0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80 --fork-url  http://localhost:8545\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\nimport \"forge-std/console.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract NonceTest is Script {\r\n    function run() external {\r\n        address alice = address(0xA11CE);\r\n        console.log(\"alice\", alice);\r\n        console.log(\"nonce\", vm.getNonce(alice));\r\n        require(vm.getNonce(alice) == 0, \"nonce should be 0\");\r\n\r\n        console.log(\"msg.sender\", msg.sender);\r\n        console.log(\"nonce\", vm.getNonce(msg.sender));\r\n        require(vm.getNonce(msg.sender) == 0, \"nonce should be 0\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n`require(vm.getNonce(msg.sender) == 0, \"nonce should be 0\");` reverts on a new anvil local chain. I passed in the first wallet keypair outputted from anvil in the `forge script` and run the script `forge script script/NonceTest.s.sol:NonceTest --private-key 0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80 --fork-url  http://localhost:8545`.\r\nI would expect the `msg.sender` being an EOA wallet has a nonce of 0 on a new chain rather than 1. Possibly confused with a contract wallet? \r\nUsing `vm.getNonce` in script gives me ability to pre calculate the contract address to be deployed.",
